'''新仙女木事件'''，也稱為'''克洛維斯彗星假說'''，是為解釋[[末次冰期|末次冰期]]之後的[[新仙女木期|新仙女木期]]的一個極具競爭性的科學假說。這個假設，科學家們還在爭辯中。他们提出當時的氣候变化是由于一顆或多顆彗星的撞擊，或是其在空中的爆炸而引发了气候的变冷<ref name="Firestone2006">{{cite book |last1=Firestone |first1=Richard |last2=West |first2=Allen |last3=Warwick-Smith |first3=Simon |title=The Cycle of Cosmic Catastrophes: How a Stone-Age Comet Changed the Course of World Culture |url=http://www.amazon.com/The-Cycle-Cosmic-Catastrophes-Stone-Age/dp/1591430615 |date=4 June 2006 |publisher=Bear & Company |isbn=1591430615 |pages=392 |access-date=2015-09-05 |archive-date=2015-09-10 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20150910132715/http://www.amazon.com/The-Cycle-Cosmic-Catastrophes-Stone-Age/dp/1591430615 |dead-url=no }}</ref><ref name="PNAS07A">{{cite journal  |vauthors=Firestone RB, West A, Kennett JP, etal |title=Evidence for an extraterrestrial impact 12,900 years ago that contributed to the megafaunal extinctions and the Younger Dryas cooling |journal=Proc. Natl. Acad. Sci. U.S.A. |volume=104 |issue=41 |pages=16016–21 |date=October 2007 |pmid=17901202 |pmc=1994902 |doi=10.1073/pnas.0706977104 |url=|bibcode = 2007PNAS..10416016F }}</ref><ref name=Bunch>{{cite journal  |vauthors=Bunch TE, Hermes RE, Moore AM, etal |title=Very high-temperature impact melt products as evidence for cosmic airbursts and impacts 12,900 years ago |journal=Proc Natl Acad Sci U S A |volume= 109|issue= 28|pages= E1903–12|date=June 2012 |pmid=22711809 |doi=10.1073/pnas.1204453109 |url=|bibcode = 2012PNAS..109E1903B }}</ref>。

一般性的假設指出，[[距今|距今]]大約12,900年前（未經<sup>14</sup>C[[放射性碳定年法#校准|校準]]前為10,900年），[[近地小行星|近地小行星]]的撞擊或空中爆炸造成[[北美洲|北美洲]]大陸地區大规模的野火，从而擾亂了氣候并造成北美洲地區的[[第四紀滅絕事件|第四紀滅絕事件]]。其結果是北美洲大多數的[[更新世巨型動物群|更新世巨型動物群]]滅絕，以及[[克洛維斯文化|克洛維斯文化]]迅速的滅亡<ref name="Kennett">{{cite journal |author=Kennett DJ, Kennett JP, West A, ''et al.'' |title=Nanodiamonds in the Younger Dryas boundary sediment layer |journal=Science |volume=323 |issue=5910 |pages=94 |date=2009-01 |pmid=19119227 |doi=10.1126/science.1162819 |url=|bibcode = 2009Sci...323...94K}}</ref>。新仙女木冰河期持續了約1,200年，随后气候才再度回暖。此一事件也被視為[[全新世滅絕事件|全新世滅絕事件]]的一部分。

在大湖區的{{le|勞倫臺德冰蓋|Laurentide Ice Sheet}}可能发生了一次或多次的大爆炸。雖然沒有鑑定到主要的陨石坑，但支持者认为这些爆炸可能发生在空中，陨石在天空上方解體，这與1908年的[[通古斯事件|通古斯事件]]相似，但規模更大<ref name= "Napier2010ras">{{cite journal |author= Napier WM |title= Palaeolithic extinctions and the Taurid Complex |journal= Monthly Notices of the Royal Astronomical Society |volume= 405 |issue= 3 |pages= 1901_1906 |date= July 2010 |url= http://onlinelibrary.wiley.com/doi/10.1111/j.1365-2966.2010.16579.x/abstract |doi= 10.1111/j.1365-2966.2010.16579.x |bibcode= 2010MNRAS.405.1901N |access-date= 2015-09-05 |archive-date= 2015-12-04 |archive-url= https://web.archive.org/web/20151204004252/http://onlinelibrary.wiley.com/doi/10.1111/j.1365-2966.2010.16579.x/abstract |dead-url= no }}</ref><ref name= "Napier2010arxiv">{{cite journal |author= Napier WM |title= Palaeolithic extinctions and the Taurid Complex |journal= arXiv |volume= arXiv:1003.0744 |date= March 2010 |url= http://arxiv.org/abs/1003.0744 |access-date= 2015-09-05 |archive-date= 2016-02-05 |archive-url= https://web.archive.org/web/20160205162317/http://arxiv.org/abs/1003.0744 |dead-url= no }}</ref>。关于這个事件個對美洲大陸生態影響的假說认为，那些生活在北美洲的動物和人類不是直接死於爆炸，就是死于因此產生的[[野火|野火]]。

大量的研究檔案指出，這個（或者这些）假設事件的影響范围超出了美洲，其影響遍及全球各大洲。例如，James Wittke 等人的文章指出这次撞擊的残骸沉積跨越四大洲，包括歐洲和中東地區<ref>{{cite journal|pages=E2088–E2097|title=Evidence for deposition of 10 million tonnes of impact spherules across four continents 12,800 y ago|volume=110|issue=23|date=2013-06-04|journal=Proceedings of the National Academy of Sciences|url=http://www.pnas.org/lookup/doi/10.1073/pnas.1301760110|accessdate=2018-04-02|author=James H. Wittke, James C. Weaver, Ted E. Bunch, James P. Kennett, Douglas J. Kennett, Andrew M. T. Moore, Gordon C. Hillman, Kenneth B. Tankersley, Albert C. Goodyear, Christopher R. Moore, I. Randolph Daniel, Jack H. Ray, Neal H. Lopinot, David Ferraro, Isabel Israde-Alcántara, James L. Bischoff, Paul S. DeCarli, Robert E. Hermes, Johan B. Kloosterman, Zsolt Revay, George A. Howard, David R. Kimbel, Gunther Kletetschka, Ladislav Nabelek, Carl P. Lipo, Sachiko Sakai, Allen West, Richard B. Firestone|doi=10.1073/pnas.1301760110}}</ref>。

== 證據 ==
陨石撞击的证据主要是來自於[[北美洲|北美洲]]平原上多个与[[克洛维斯文化|克洛维斯文化]]遗迹同期、富含有机物的[[地层|地层]]，学说提倡者在这些地层发现了纳米钻石、陨石微[[球晶|球晶]]、碳球晶、磁球晶、[[铱|铱]]、[[铂|铂]]、异常的[[铂|铂]]/[[钯|钯]]比例、[[木炭|木炭]]、[[煤烟|煤烟]]以及富含[[氦-3|氦-3]]的[[富勒烯|富勒烯]]等，这些不寻常的物质分布只能是[[撞击事件|撞击事件]]所产生，并标志了[[新仙女木期|新仙女木期]]的起始<ref name="Dalton">{{Cite journal|title=Blast in the past?|url=https://www.nature.com/articles/447256a|last=Dalton|first=Rex|date=2007-05-01|journal=Nature|issue=7142|doi=10.1038/447256a|volume=447|pages=256–257|language=en|issn=1476-4687|access-date=2022-02-14|archive-date=2022-03-20|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20220320052719/https://www.nature.com/articles/447256a}}</ref><ref name="Wittke b">{{cite journal | vauthors = Wittke JH, Weaver JC, Bunch TE, Kennett JP, Kennett DJ, Moore AM, Hillman GC, Tankersley KB, Goodyear AC, Moore CR, Daniel IR, Ray JH, Lopinot NH, Ferraro D, Israde-Alcántara I, Bischoff JL, DeCarli PS, Hermes RE, Kloosterman JB, Revay Z, Howard GA, Kimbel DR, Kletetschka G, Nabelek L, Lipo CP, Sakai S, West A, Firestone RB | display-authors = 6 | title = Evidence for deposition of 10 million tonnes of impact spherules across four continents 12,800 y ago | journal = Proceedings of the National Academy of Sciences of the United States of America | volume = 110 | issue = 23 | pages = E2088–97 | date = June 2013 | pmid = 23690611 | pmc = 3677428 | doi = 10.1073/pnas.1301760110 | bibcode = 2013PNAS..110E2088W }}</ref>。火山、人类活动或其它自然作用无法解释这些现象。{{r|Bunch}}

== 撞击后果 ==
